                <h1>Understanding Fork Transparency: Enhance Collaboration</h1>
                <p>Fork transparent refers to a process in software development, especially in version control systems like Git. It allows developers to see changes made in different branches without cluttering the main codebase. This feature enhances collaboration, enabling teams to efficiently manage updates, resolve conflicts, and maintain code quality.</p>
